    }
  ],
  
  benefitCards: [
    {
      icon: "globe",
      title: "Source country expertise",
      text: "We know the specific requirements for documents from major source countries."
    },
    {
      icon: "shield",
      title: "Complete coordination",
      text: "We manage the entire chain so you do not need to track multiple agencies."
    },
    {
      icon: "clock",
      title: "Timeline clarity",
      text: "Realistic timeframes upfront based on document type and source country."
    }
  ],
  
  accordionSections: [
    {
      title: "Understanding the attestation chain",
      id: "chain",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Hague Convention countries (Apostille)",
          body: "<p>If your document is from a country that signed the Hague Convention (UK, USA, EU, Australia, Canada, India, and 100+ others), it can be Apostilled. An Apostille is a simplified certification that replaces traditional embassy legalization for these countries.</p><p>After Apostille in your home country, the document goes directly to MOFA attestation in UAE. This is faster and less expensive than the traditional route.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Non-Hague countries (Embassy attestation)",
          body: "<p>If your document is from a country that has not joined the Hague Convention, the traditional attestation chain applies: notary attestation, foreign affairs attestation in your country, UAE Embassy attestation in your country, then MOFA attestation in UAE.</p><p>This process takes longer but we coordinate with verified partners in major source countries to manage the complete chain.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Documents requiring translation first",
          body: "<p>Some documents need translation before attestation. For example, if your <a href='/personal/vital-records/birth/'>birth certificate</a> is in a language other than Arabic or English, it may need certified translation before the attestation chain begins.</p><p>We provide both translation and attestation services, ensuring the correct sequence is followed.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "MOFA attestation (final step)",
          body: "<p>MOFA (Ministry of Foreign Affairs) attestation is the final step that makes your document valid for use in UAE. Without this step, the document will not be accepted by UAE government authorities, courts, or employers.</p><p>We handle MOFA submission and collection, delivering the fully attested document to you.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Common attestation scenarios",
      id: "scenarios",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Degree for employment",
          body: "<p>UAE employers and MOHRE require <a href='/personal/education/degree/'>degree certificates</a> to be attested for work permit applications. The complete chain includes: university verification, home country attestation or Apostille, UAE Embassy attestation (if applicable), and MOFA attestation.</p><p>We handle the complete process, advising you on any additional steps specific to your country and field.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Marriage certificate for visa",
          body: "<p>Sponsoring a spouse requires an attested <a href='/personal/vital-records/marriage/'>marriage certificate</a>. If the marriage took place outside UAE, the certificate needs attestation through the complete chain before immigration authorities will accept it.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Commercial documents for business",
          body: "<p><a href='/legal/corporate/moa/'>MOA</a>, trade licenses, and commercial contracts may need attestation for use in UAE business transactions or government tenders. The requirements vary based on the intended use.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Golden Visa documents",
          body: "<p>For <a href='/services/golden-visa-translation/'>Golden Visa applications</a>, multiple documents often require attestation including degrees, police clearances, and family certificates.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Related services",
      id: "related",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Legal translation",
          body: "<p>Our <a href='/services/legal-translation/'>legal translation services</a> ensure your documents are correctly translated with MOJ certification before or after attestation as required.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Corporate documents",
          body: "<p>For <a href='/services/corporate-translation/'>corporate translation</a> and attestation of business documents, we coordinate the complete process.</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  
  faqs: [
    {
      question: "Do you handle the entire attestation process or just the UAE part?",
      answer: "We handle the complete chain. If your document needs home country attestation first, we coordinate with verified partners in major source countries to ensure the entire process is managed seamlessly."
    },
    {
      question: "What is the difference between Apostille and Embassy attestation?",
      answer: "An Apostille is a simplified certification valid between countries that signed the Hague Convention. If your document is from a Hague country (UK, USA, EU, Australia, etc.), an Apostille replaces embassy attestation - it is often faster and less expensive."
    },
    {
      question: "How long does the complete attestation chain take?",
      answer: "Timelines vary by source country and document type. Apostille from Hague countries typically takes 2-4 weeks. Traditional embassy attestation from non-Hague countries may take 4-8 weeks. We provide realistic timeframes based on your specific situation."
    },
    {
      question: "Can you attest documents that are already translated?",
      answer: "Yes, if the translation was done by an MOJ-licensed translator. If the translation is from another source, we may need to re-translate it to meet UAE requirements."
    }
  ],
  serviceType: "Document Attestation"
};
---

<ServiceLayout {...pageData}>
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Service Levels</h2>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>MOFA Only</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 300</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">When document is already embassy-attested</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card pricing-card--featured">
          <h3>Complete Chain</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 800</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">Source country to MOFA</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>Translation + Attestation</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">From AED 500</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">When translation needed first</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServiceLayout>

<style>
  .pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .pricing-card { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 1rem; padding: 2rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); }
  .pricing-card--featured { border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(255, 22, 84, 0.15); background: #ffffff; }
  .pricing-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .pricing-price { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary-color); }
  .pricing-time { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
